        xmlns:d="http://schemas.microsoft.com/expression/blend/2008"
        xmlns:mc="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/markup-compatibility/2006"
        xmlns:local="clr-namespace:Library.Views"
        mc:Ignorable="d"
        Title="AboutLibraryWindow" Height="450" Width="800">
    <Grid>
        <Image Source="C:\Users\Shokhruz\Desktop\Library\SolutionLibrary\Library\Views\Required images\imresizer-1719607846103.jpg"
               Stretch="UniformToFill"/>
        <TextBlock
            Text="Mashennik's Library is a mythical place celebrated for its enchanting collection and mysterious aura. Nestled in a secluded corner of an ancient city, it is steeped in legends and captivating tales. Here are some fascinating aspects of Mashennik's Library:"/>

        <TextBlock
            Text="1. Origin: Founded by the enigmatic scholar Mashennik, renowned for his studies in alchemy and ancient wisdom, the library has a rich and intriguing history.

            2. Collection: The library houses rare and unique books, manuscripts, and scrolls. Many of these contain forgotten knowledge and ancient spells, making it a treasure trove for seekers of wisdom.

            3. Architecture: The library is an architectural marvel, featuring Gothic-style high arches, stained glass windows, and narrow corridors. Its interior exudes grandeur and a mystical ambiance.

            4. Secrets: It's said that the library is full of hidden rooms, secret passages, and clever traps. Only a few can navigate their way to the most precious tomes.

            5. Guardianship: The library is protected by magical guardians, and legends suggest that Mashennik himself cast spells to safeguard his collection.

            6. Visitors: Only the chosen few are granted access. Those with a pure heart and a quest for knowledge find answers to their deepest questions here.

            7. Loan Policy: When borrowing a book from the library, there is a 10-day return period. This time is considered sufficient to study the rare knowledge without allowing it to leave the library for too long.

            Mashennik's Library remains an enigmatic beacon of knowledge, its true contents and purpose shrouded in positive intrigue and wonder."
            Background="AntiqueWhite"
            TextWrapping="Wrap">
            
        </TextBlock>
    </Grid>
</Window>
